You can also:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul dir=\"auto\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ereview pull requests\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ehelp us stay on top of new and old issues\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003edevelop tutorials, presentations, and other educational materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003emaintain and improve \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/numpy/numpy.org\"\u003eour website\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003edevelop graphic design for our brand assets and promotional materials\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003etranslate website content\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ehelp with outreach and onboard new contributors\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ewrite grant proposals and help with other fundraising efforts\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp dir=\"auto\"\u003eFor more information about the ways you can contribute to NumPy, visit \u003ca href=\"https://numpy.org/contribute/\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eour website\u003c/a\u003e.\nIf you’re unsure where to start or how your skills fit in, reach out! <p dir="auto">NumPy is the fundamental package for scientific computing with Python.</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="https://numpy.org" rel="nofollow">https://numpy.org</a></li>
<li><strong>Documentation:</strong> <a href="https://numpy.org/doc" rel="nofollow">https://numpy.org/doc</a></li>
<li><strong>Mailing list:</strong> <a href="https://mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/numpy-discussion" rel="nofollow">https://mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/numpy-discussion</a></li>
<li><strong>Source code:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/numpy/numpy">https://github.com/numpy/numpy</a></li>
<li><strong>Contributing:</strong> <a href="https://numpy.org/devdocs/dev/index.html" rel="nofollow">https://numpy.org/devdocs/dev/index.html</a></li>
<li><strong>Bug reports:</strong> <a href="https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues">https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues</a></li>
<li><strong>Report a security vulnerability:</strong> <a href="https://tidelift.com/docs/security" rel="nofollow">https://tidelift.com/docs/security</a></li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">It provides:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>a powerful N-dimensional array object</li>
<li>sophisticated (broadcasting) functions</li>
<li>tools for integrating C/C++ and Fortran code</li>
<li>useful linear algebra, Fourier transform, and random number capabilities</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">Testing:</p>
<p dir="auto">NumPy requires <code>pytest</code> and <code>hypothesis</code>.  Tests can then be run after installation with:</p>
<div class="snippet-clipboard-content notranslate position-relative overflow-auto" data-snippet-clipboard-copy-content="python -c "import numpy, sys; sys.exit(numpy.test() is False)""><pre class="notranslate"><code>python -c "import numpy, sys; sys.exit(numpy.test() is False)"
</code></pre></div>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Code of Conduct</h2><a id="user-content-code-of-conduct" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Code of Conduct" href="#code-of-conduct"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">NumPy is a community-driven open source project developed by a diverse group of
<a href="https://numpy.org/teams/" rel="nofollow">contributors</a>. The NumPy leadership has made a strong
commitment to creating an open, inclusive, and positive community. Please read the
<a href="https://numpy.org/code-of-conduct/" rel="nofollow">NumPy Code of Conduct</a> for guidance on how to interact
with others in a way that makes our community thrive.</p>
<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Call for Contributions</h2><a id="user-content-call-for-contributions" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Call for Contributions" href="#call-for-contributions"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">The NumPy project welcomes your expertise and enthusiasm!</p>
<p dir="auto">Small improvements or fixes are always appreciated. If you are considering larger contributions
to the source code, please contact us through the <a href="https://mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/numpy-discussion" rel="nofollow">mailing
list</a> first.</p>
<p dir="auto">Writing code isn’t the only way to contribute to NumPy. You can also:</p>
<ul dir="auto">
<li>review pull requests</li>
<li>help us stay on top of new and old issues</li>
<li>develop tutorials, presentations, and other educational materials</li>
<li>maintain and improve <a href="https://github.com/numpy/numpy.org">our website</a></li>
<li>develop graphic design for our brand assets and promotional materials</li>
<li>translate website content</li>
<li>help with outreach and onboard new contributors</li>
<li>write grant proposals and help with other fundraising efforts</li>
</ul>
<p dir="auto">For more information about the ways you can contribute to NumPy, visit <a href="https://numpy.org/contribute/" rel="nofollow">our website</a>.
If you’re unsure where to start or how your skills fit in, reach out! You can
ask on the mailing list or here, on GitHub, by opening a new issue or leaving a
comment on a relevant issue that is already open.</p>
<p dir="auto">Our preferred channels of communication are all public, but if you’d like to
speak to us in private first, contact our community coordinators at
<a href="mailto:numpy-team@googlegroups.com">numpy-team@googlegroups.com</a> or on Slack (write <a href="mailto:numpy-team@googlegroups.com">numpy-team@googlegroups.com</a> for
an invitation).</p>
<p dir="auto">We also have a biweekly community call, details of which are announced on the
mailing list. You are very welcome to join.</p>
<p dir="auto">If you are new to contributing to open source, <a href="https://opensource.guide/how-to-contribute/" rel="nofollow">this
guide</a> helps explain why, what,
and how to successfully get involved.</p>
